This paper discusses the use of blockchain technology for data accountability and provenance tracking, which are topics related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of contracts to encode data usage policies, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of the proposed approach, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE).
